library(ppcor)
## Loading required package: MASS
library(treeducken)
## Loading required package: ape
# read r and p values
rp <- read.table("rpHommola_1010.txt", header = TRUE)
# p values
Ps <- rp[, 2]
#replace 0s with 1e-6
Ps[Ps == 0] <- 1e-6
# read r values
rH <- rp[, 1]

#Examine values
boxplot(rp)

# Get trees to compute Ne (no. effective pairs)
cophylSim <- readRDS("03_cophylSim1010.rds")
# extract trees - ultrametric
TreeH <- lapply(cophylSim, host_tree)
TreeS <- lapply(cophylSim, symb_tree)
# drop extinct taxa
TreeH <- lapply(TreeH, drop_extinct)
TreeS <- lapply(TreeS, drop_extinct)

# Number of host & symb taxa
Nh <- sapply(1:length(TreeH), function(x) TreeH[[x]]$Nnode+1)
Ns <- sapply(1:length(TreeS), function(x) TreeS[[x]]$Nnode+1)
# Number of effective pairs
Ne <- 2 * Ns * Nh / (Ns + Nh)
# degrees of freedom
df <- Ne-2
# Convert p values into t values 
# t values
t.values <- mapply(qt, Ps, df)
# Compute Req
R.eq <- sqrt(t.values**2/(t.values**2 + df))
VarR.eq <- (1-R.eq)**2/(Ne-1)
# compute related z scores
Zr <- 0.5 * log((1 + R.eq) / (1 - R.eq))
VarZr <- 1 /(Ne-3)
###############################
# CHECK CORRELATION p WITH COEV EVENTS
co.ev <- read.table("03_nrEvents1010.txt")
plot(co.ev$CSP, R.eq)

plot(co.ev$CSP, Zr)

# cor.test(co.ev$CSP, Zr, method = "spearman")
cor.test(co.ev$CSP, R.eq, method = "spearman")
## Warning in cor.test.default(co.ev$CSP, R.eq, method = "spearman"): Cannot
## compute exact p-value with ties

# check correlation with proportion CSP/total n events
Sevents <- apply(co.ev, 1, sum)

plot(co.ev$CSP/Sevents, R.eq)
